diff:1669580386:1669225849:=87,104d86%0a%3c #foxbegin 221127-201949-881410#%0a%3c (:div1 class=expansionhead:)%0a%3c !!!Facial Tracking tech in Sign Language %0a%3c -> - aarnavp%0a%3c -> [-27.11.2022 - 12:19-]%0a%3c >>rfloat%3c%3c   %0a%3c (:if1 authgroup @tas:)%0a%3c {[foxdelrange button 221127-201949-881410 {$FullName} ]}%0a%3c (:if1end:)%0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c (:div1end:) %0a%3c >>messageitem%3c%3c %0a%3c On the topic of facial expressions in sign language, new technologies have made it possible to hyper analyze the degree of characteristic facial expressions in overall meaning. In a study conducted in the context of Kazakh-Russo Sign Language, researchers were able to track eyebrow movement to see its correlation with emotion and interrogative questions. This creates the potential to analyze the eyebrow movement from signs within a sentence, and understand the complex system facial expressions play with this larger sign language system. It’s interesting to note the similarities between sign language and spoken language, where facial expressions can apply for multiple different moods within a sentence. %0a%3c %0a%3c 1)uib.no/en/hf/136874/complex-system-facial-expressions-sign-language#:~:text="In%2520sign%2520language%252C%2520facial%2520expressions,or%2520when%2520quoting%2520someone%2520else.%0a%3c %0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c #foxend 221127-201949-881410#%0a
